name: Paula Shugart
bio: Former president of @missuniverse | advocate for women across the globe

social_posts.post_text: Only in New Orleans!  Great way to start the day.
null
In my room, curled up with some really interesting reading… The Miss Universe Delegate Profile Book……. #71stmissuniverse #visitneworleans
@thejeanniemai @oliviaculpo two of my favorite ladies taking the stage!!
Waiting for Final question!

Sitting after the show, waiting for the press conference to begin. Thanks to everyone who worked so hard to pull off a beautiful event. Amazing production team and a special thanks to @jovanifashions for always making me feel comfortable and glamorous at the same time. Nothing like a big, fluffy dress with POCKETS!

Today, I am incredibly saddened to learn of the passing of a very special person. Angelo Lambrou was an award winning designer (he designed and made the dress Mpule Kwelagobe wore when she won Miss Universe - actually he made it twice when the first was lost in customs). More importantly, Angelo just had the most positive outlook, no matter the circumstance.  He possessed an inherent innocence and belief in the good of people, which made him a joy to be around.  He was gifted, brilliant, kind and giving.  When Carl and I decided to have a surprise wedding at a luau in our home, Angelo was one of the few who knew, and he insisted on making a dress for me in a matter of days. You will be missed, sweet Angelo.  My thoughts and love to your family and husband.

So saddened to hear to news of Miss Universe 1970, Marisol Malaret’s passing. I met her when she judged for us in Puerto Rico. I had just become president.  She could not have been more gracious and helpful, sitting with me for hours and answering all of my questions and giving me her candid advice. She was a very special woman, the embodiment of beautifully confident. #RIPMarisol
Carl proudly raising the SDSU colors in anticipation of today’s big game. #goaztecs

Having fun at the #globalbeautyawards with these two amazing ladies!  Love you @amyemmerich and @denisewhite_eag congratulations to all of the nominees and lifetime achievement award recipient, Amy Emmerich.

I could not be more excited to read the latest book from one of the most inspirational women I know, @jamiekernlima. Jamie’s last book, “Believe It” helped me through a very difficult time in my life and I will be the first in line to read #Worthy. Worthybook.com. Very proud to say she was a former Miss Washington USA.  Thanks, Jamie for all you do to help others realize their potential.
Beautiful Basel!
You never know where a message is going to appear. This one on a wall in Lucerne.
Beautiful Labor Day sailing through Charleston Harbor with my best friend! #blessed

Thank you President Bukele @nayibbukele for hosting @annejkn.official and our delegation to discuss the final preparations for the 72nd Miss Universe. We are so grateful for your support and the support of all the people of El Salvador. The team you have assembled is one of the most professional I have ever worked with and I know the event will be spectacular. Looking forward to showcasing the new El Salvador to the world. Two weeks until delegate arrivals!!
The best part of my job is all of the truly incredible women I have been able to meet over the years. A wonderful evening with a great friend. Loved seeing you @bui.simon

Viva El Salvador!  Gracias por todo!

Goodbye, Universe!  Thank you for the greatest adventure anyone could ever wish for. It has been an honor and a privilege to guide this brand as president through thick and thin for over 20 years.  Thank you to our fans, directors and the amazing titleholders I have been blessed to meet throughout the years.  You are what makes Miss Universe great!  I love you all!  And to avoid speculation…… I am definitely not retiring.  I will see you all soon! ❤️

It’s such an honor to have the opportunity to close the 72nd Miss Universe doing the Hair and Makeup of the REAL QUEEN of this brand @realpaulashugart 
She has become a legend in beauty pageants and we were here to live her last show with her! A very big dream to us!
